  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then boil a full kettle</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into bite-sized chunks</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>and chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616676897967-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616676897967-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616676897967-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616676897967-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616676897967-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616676901848-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616676901848-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616676901848-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616676901848-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616676901848-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616676906005-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616676906005-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616676906005-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616676906005-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616676906005-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, roughly chop your <strong>black</strong> <strong>olives</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 3-4 min</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> </strong>200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>to the pan and cook, covered, for 15 min or until reduced to a stew-like consistency – this is your <strong>Provençal-style sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616676910020-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616676910020-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616676910020-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616676910020-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616676910020-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind the <strong>chopped black olives</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a smooth paste (alternatively, pulse in a <strong>food processor </strong>until smooth)</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>black olive</strong> <strong>tapenade</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616676923889-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616676923889-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616676923889-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616676923889-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616676923889-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>tin foil</strong>, then place your<strong> salmon</strong> <strong>fillet[s]</strong> on the tray (or two!), skin-side down</p><p>Divide and spread the <strong>black olive</strong> <strong>tapenade</strong> over the salmon</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 14-15 min or until the fish is cooked through – this is your<strong> black olive</strong> <strong>tapenade baked salmon</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616676933004-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616676933004-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616676933004-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616676933004-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616676933004-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a splash of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and mash until smooth</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
